getNFTCollectionPrice(address).details: gets the price of an NFT Collection. It will return the NFT Collection price to be used for each token Id (i.e. Floor Price).

params.nftContract: is the address of the NFT contract

getNFTPrice(address,uint256).details: gets the price of an NFT. It will return the NFT's specific price, or the price of the collection if no specific price has been given

params.nftContract: is the address of the NFT contract

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setNFTCollectionPrice(address,uint256).details: set the price for whole collection. If an NFT has a price specific for it, the collection price would have the second priority.

params.nftContract: is the address of the NFT contract

setSingleNFTPrice(address,uint256,uint25.details: set the price for a single NFT from a collection

params.nftContract: is the address of the NFT contract

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

version().details: gets the version of the contract
